cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about natural language generation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The model presented in the paper uses a combination of stochastic and corpus-based approaches, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The model also uses dependency relations to generate natural language text, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance using evaluation metrics commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
